headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 33 points and John Collins hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with 24.4 seconds remaining Wednesday night, rallying Atlanta to a 120-116 victory over the Washington Wizards to...
headlines.shortLinkText: Young rallies Hawks to playoff berth, 120-116 over Wizards

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — James Harden had 18 points and 11 assists in his return from an 18-game absence to help the Brooklyn Nets beat the San Antonio Spurs 128-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden returns to score 18 points, Nets beat Spurs 128-116

headlines.description: — Kevin Love scored a season-high 30 points, Collin Sexton added 28 and the Cleveland Cavaliers snapped an 11-game losing streak with a 102-94 win in their home finale over Boston on Wednesday night, locking the Celtics into a spot in the NBA's...
headlines.shortLinkText: Love scores 30, Cavs beat Celtics to end 11-game slide

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 33 points, Kristaps Porzingis added 19 in his return from injury and the Dallas Mavericks took a big step toward avoiding the play-in tournament with a 125-107 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs get key 125-107 win for postseason, eliminate Pelicans

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 30 points and CJ McCollum added 26 to lead the Portland Trail Blazers to a 105-98 victory over the Utah Jazz on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blazers win fifth straight, beat Jazz 105-98

events.name: Houston Rockets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma's driving layup with 6.9 seconds remaining gave the short-handed Los Angeles Lakers a 124-122 victory over the Houston Rockets on Tuesday night and kept the defending NBA champions' slim hopes of avoiding the play-in tournament alive.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma's late basket gives Lakers 3rd straight win
